item.ptxt: “MIL” column in table below indicates MIL is applicable or not when corresponding DTC is detected.
For identification of each cylinder and bank, refer to Precaution for Identification of Cylinder and Bank:N32A .
For type definition of OBD system, refer to Precaution on On-Board Diagnostic (OBD) System:N32A .
With the CAN communication generic scan tool, only asterisk (*) marked DTC in the following table can be read.

When DTC P0300 / P0301 / P0302 / P0303 / P0304 / P0305 / P0306 is detected, MIL blinks or lights up according to detecting condition. For details, refer to DTC P0300 / P0301 / P0302 / P0303 / P0304 / P0305 / P0306:N32A .
*1: For DTC with asterisk 1 (*1) in the table below, it is applicable to type A OBD system.

*2: For DTC detection logic with asterisk 2 (*2) in the table below, it is necessary to perform the DTC confirmation procedure several times in order to complete the diagnosing when the past measurements are deleted.
For details, refer to the following.
